snippet: A record six teams are paying baseball's luxury tax this season, led by the Los Angeles Dodgers at $31.8 million and the New York Yankees at $27.4 million....
lead_paragraph: A record six teams are paying baseball's luxury tax this season, led by the Los Angeles Dodgers at $31.8 million and the New York Yankees at $27.4 million.

headline.main: APNewsBreak: Record 6 MLB Teams to Pay Luxury Tax
